   Main Page Content

VA Nurse

   Call the VA Nurse if you need healthcare advice 24 hours a day, 7 days
   a week, at 1-866-NURSE VA (1-866-687-7382).
     * When should I call the VA Nurse?

     If you have healthcare questions before your next clinic
     appointment, call the VA Nurse.  You can call the VA Nurse day or
     night if:
     * You are worried about a health problem.
     * You have a healthcare question.
     * You are feeling sick.
     * You are hurt.
     * You aren't sure if you should make an appointment.
     * You aren't sure if you should go to an Emergency Room.
     * You are coming to the VA without an appointment.

     * What will the VA Nurse ask me?

     The VA Nurse will ask:
     * Your name.
     * Your social security number.
     * Your telephone number and area code.
     * At which VA site of care do you routinely receive primary care
       services.
     * What is the name of your healthcare provider or team.
     * The list of medications you are taking.
     * How you are feeling.
     * Your symptoms.

   The VA Nurse may give you advice for home care or you may be directed
   to other healthcare services.

     In the case of a life-threatening emergency, call 911 immediately.

   *The VA Nurse does not authorize payment for care received at a non-VA
                                  facility.
